
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Note - FAQ";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

<!-- Head -->
<section id="head">
    <div id="page-head-content">
        <div class="page-text">
            <p>Frequently Asked Questions</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>


<!-- FAQ -->
<section id="faqs">
    <div class="content-box">
        <!-- General Question -->
        <div class="container">
            <div class="title">
                <p>General Questions</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-collapse">
                <button class="collapsible">What is Notes Marketplace?</button>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>
                        Notes Marketplace is an online marketplace for university students to buy and sell their
                        course notes.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-collapse">
                <button class="collapsible">What is Notes Marketplace?</button>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>
                        Notes Marketplace is an online marketplace for university students to buy and sell their
                        course notes.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Uploader -->
        <div class="container uploader">
            <div class="title">
                <p>Uploaders</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-collapse">
                <button class="collapsible">Why should I upload now?</button>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>
                        To maximize sales. We can't sell your notes if they are rotting on your hard drive. Your
                        notes are available for purchase the instant they are approved, which means that you could be missing potential sales as we speak. Despite exam and holiday breaks, our users purchase notes all year round, so the best time to upload notes is always today.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-collapse">
                <button class="collapsible">What can't I sell?</button>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>We won't approve materials that have been created by your university or another third party. We also do not accept assignments, essays, practical’s or take-home exams. We love notes though.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-collapse">
                <button class="collapsible">How long does it take to upload?</button>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>Uploading notes is quick and easy. It can take as little as 90 seconds per set of notes. Put it this way, in the time it took to read these FAQs, you could’ve uploaded several sets of notes.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Downloader -->
        <div class="container downloader">
            <div class="title">
                <p>Downloaders</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-collapse">
                <button class="collapsible">How do I buy notes?</button>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>Search for the notes you are after using the 'SEARCH NOTES' tab at the at the top right of every page. You can then filter results by university, category, course information etc. To purchase, go to detail page of note and click on download button. If notes are free to download – it will download over the browser and if notes are paid, Once Seller will allow download you can have notes at my downloads grid for actual download.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-collapse">
                <button class="collapsible">Why should I buy notes?</button>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>The notes on our site are incredibly useful as an educational tool when used correctly. They effectively demonstrate the techniques that top students employ in order to receive top marks. They also summaries the course in a concise format and show what that student believed were the most important elements of the course. Learn from the best.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-collapse">
                <button class="collapsible">Will downloading notes guarantee I improve my grades?</button>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>How long is a piece of string? However, 90% of students who purchased notes through our site said that doing so improved their grades.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</section>

